EXTRACTED VALUE: The players move nicely, and their personal touches are great, including Rip Hamilton's free throw ritual to Shawn Marion's unique jump shot.
The best way to describe Vegas 2 is that it’s not really a full sequel — it’s just the rest of the first game.
Blue Dragon is a harmless, lighthearted role-playing game at its core with too many cutscenes but with some really great strategic battles.
Castle Crashers is an entertaining brawler, but the replay value is chopped into little frustrating bits by a horrifically painful online experience.
The Nail the Trick mode is the evolution the game has been waiting for, and it alone is enough to recommend the game.
Where most super-hero games are satisfied with mediocrity, Marvel: Ultimate Alliance aims high and blasts its target into smithereens. 'Nuff said!
If you are a fan of the genre and have been hoping for something new and fresh, this will suit you quite nicely.
EA has succeeded in taking the game back to its roots, but in other ways not as far as some may have liked.
Prey offers a surreal and entertaining playing experience; however I did feel that it was a one trick pony, albeit a very good trick indeed.
Fight Night is a fantastic game that even after the short career mode, will keep you going with it’s hard hitting and intense multiplayer.
Pure doesn't blaze many new trails, but this off-road racer still delivers an intense, tricked-out thrill ride.
